{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":978,"text":"So have you ever wondered\nwhat it would be like"},{"time":4104,"text":"to live in a place with no rules?"},{"time":7833,"text":"That sounds pretty cool."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9008,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":10070,"text":"You wake up one morning, however,"},{"time":11731,"text":"and you discover that the reason\nthere are no rules"},{"time":14235,"text":"is because there's no government,\nand there are no laws."},{"time":17620,"text":"In fact, all social institutions\nhave disappeared."},{"time":22918,"text":"So there's no schools,"},{"time":24275,"text":"there's no hospitals,"},{"time":25465,"text":"there's no police,"},{"time":26797,"text":"there's no banks,"},{"time":28156,"text":"there's no athletic clubs,"},{"time":30734,"text":"there's no utilities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32884,"text":"Well, I know a little bit\nabout what this is like,"},{"time":36100,"text":"because when I was\na medical student in 1999,"},{"time":38973,"text":"I worked in a refugee camp\nin the Balkans during the Kosovo War."},{"time":45009,"text":"When the war was over,"},{"time":46183,"text":"I got permission -- unbelievably --\nfrom my medical school"},{"time":49265,"text":"to take some time off"},{"time":50440,"text":"and follow some of the families\nthat I had befriended in the camp"},{"time":54635,"text":"back to their village in Kosovo,"},{"time":57082,"text":"and understand how they navigated\nlife in this postwar setting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64511,"text":"Postwar Kosovo\nwas a very interesting place"},{"time":67755,"text":"because NATO troops were there,"},{"time":70948,"text":"mostly to make sure\nthe war didn't break out again."},{"time":74608,"text":"But other than that,\nit was actually a lawless place,"},{"time":78125,"text":"and almost every social institution,\nboth public and private,"},{"time":81414,"text":"had been destroyed."},{"time":83619,"text":"So I can tell you"},{"time":87532,"text":"that when you go into one\nof these situations and settings,"},{"time":92071,"text":"it is absolutely thrilling ..."},{"time":95902,"text":"for about 30 minutes,"},{"time":97278,"text":"because that's about how long it takes\nbefore you run into a situation"},{"time":101974,"text":"where you realize\nhow incredibly vulnerable you are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107720,"text":"For me, that moment came\nwhen I had to cross the first checkpoint,"},{"time":111511,"text":"and I realized as I drove up"},{"time":113328,"text":"that I would be negotiating passage\nthrough this checkpoint"},{"time":117450,"text":"with a heavily armed individual"},{"time":119688,"text":"who, if he decided to shoot me\nright then and there,"},{"time":123098,"text":"actually wouldn't be doing\nanything illegal."},{"time":126991,"text":"But the sense of vulnerability that I had\nwas absolutely nothing"},{"time":131878,"text":"in comparison to the vulnerability\nof the families that I got to know"},{"time":135800,"text":"over that year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137484,"text":"You see, life in a society\nwhere there are no social institutions"},{"time":142621,"text":"is riddled with danger and uncertainty,"},{"time":146089,"text":"and simple questions like,\n\"What are we going to eat tonight?\""},{"time":150425,"text":"are very complicated to answer."},{"time":154739,"text":"Questions about security,\nwhen you don't have any security systems,"},{"time":159113,"text":"are terrifying."},{"time":160555,"text":"Is that altercation I had\nwith the neighbor down the block"},{"time":163342,"text":"going to turn into a violent episode\nthat will end my life"},{"time":166180,"text":"or my family's life?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":168023,"text":"Health concerns\nwhen there is no health system"},{"time":170973,"text":"are also terrifying."},{"time":173294,"text":"I listened as many families\nhad to sort through questions like,"},{"time":176936,"text":"\"My infant has a fever.\nWhat am I going to do?\""},{"time":180423,"text":"\"My sister, who is pregnant,\nis bleeding. What should I do?"},{"time":184127,"text":"Who should I turn to?\""},{"time":185325,"text":"\"Where are the doctors,\nwhere are the nurses?"},{"time":187479,"text":"If I could find one, are they trustworthy?"},{"time":190264,"text":"How will I pay them?\nIn what currency will I pay them?\""},{"time":193021,"text":"\"If I need medications,\nwhere will I find them?"},{"time":196844,"text":"If I take those medications,\nare they actually counterfeits?\""},{"time":199763,"text":"And on and on."},{"time":202945,"text":"So for life in these settings,"},{"time":205341,"text":"the dominant theme,\nthe dominant feature of life,"},{"time":209845,"text":"is the incredible vulnerability\nthat people have to manage"},{"time":213812,"text":"day in and day out,"},{"time":215385,"text":"because of the lack of social systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218243,"text":"And it actually turns out"},{"time":219503,"text":"that this feature of life\nis incredibly difficult to explain"},{"time":223554,"text":"and be understood by people\nwho are living outside of it."},{"time":227221,"text":"I discovered this when I left Kosovo."},{"time":231881,"text":"I came back to Boston,\nI became a physician,"},{"time":235110,"text":"I became a global public\nhealth policy researcher."},{"time":239145,"text":"I joined the Harvard Medical School"},{"time":240959,"text":"and Brigham and Women's Hospital\nDivision of Global Health."},{"time":243825,"text":"And I, as a researcher,"},{"time":245083,"text":"really wanted to get started\non this problem right away."},{"time":247761,"text":"I was like, \"How do we reduce\nthe crushing vulnerability"},{"time":251353,"text":"of people living in these types\nof fragile settings?"},{"time":255148,"text":"Is there any way\nwe can start to think about"},{"time":257641,"text":"how to protect and quickly recover"},{"time":260370,"text":"the institutions\nthat are critical to survival,"},{"time":263203,"text":"like the health system?\""},{"time":264740,"text":"And I have to say,\nI had amazing colleagues."},{"time":268582,"text":"But one interesting thing about it was,"},{"time":270492,"text":"this was sort of an unusual\nquestion for them."},{"time":273000,"text":"They were kind of like,\n\"Oh, if you work in war,"},{"time":275333,"text":"doesn't that mean\nyou work on refugee camps,"},{"time":277606,"text":"and you work on documenting\nmass atrocities?\" --"},{"time":280062,"text":"which is, by the way, very,\nvery, very important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283477,"text":"So it took me a while to explain\nwhy I was so passionate about this issue,"},{"time":288655,"text":"until about six years ago."},{"time":290370,"text":"That's when this landmark study"},{"time":292459,"text":"that looked at and described\nthe public health consequences of war"},{"time":296592,"text":"was published."},{"time":297958,"text":"They came to an incredible,\nprovocative conclusion."},{"time":303851,"text":"These researchers concluded"},{"time":306524,"text":"that the vast majority of death\nand disability from war"},{"time":310022,"text":"happens after the cessation of conflict."},{"time":312679,"text":"So the most dangerous time to be a person\nliving in a conflict-affected state"},{"time":317741,"text":"is after the cessation of hostilities;"},{"time":319808,"text":"it's after the peace deal has been signed."},{"time":321833,"text":"It's when that political solution\nhas been achieved."},{"time":324418,"text":"That seems so puzzling,\nbut of course it's not,"},{"time":327976,"text":"because war kills people\nby robbing them of their clinics,"},{"time":333805,"text":"of their hospitals,"},{"time":335006,"text":"of their supply chains."},{"time":336894,"text":"Their doctors are targeted, are killed;\nthey're on the run."},{"time":340509,"text":"And more invisible\nand yet more deadly is the destruction"},{"time":344452,"text":"of the health governance institutions\nand their finances."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349118,"text":"So this is really not\nsurprising at all to me."},{"time":353790,"text":"But what is surprising\nand somewhat dismaying,"},{"time":356364,"text":"is how little impact this insight has had,"},{"time":360362,"text":"in terms of how we think\nabout human suffering and war."},{"time":364679,"text":"Let me give you a couple examples."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367106,"text":"Last year, you may remember,"},{"time":369041,"text":"Ebola hit the West African\ncountry of Liberia."},{"time":374161,"text":"There was a lot of reporting\nabout this group, Doctors Without Borders,"},{"time":378053,"text":"sounding the alarm\nand calling for aid and assistance."},{"time":381502,"text":"But not a lot of that reporting\nanswered the question:"},{"time":385388,"text":"Why is Doctors Without Borders\neven in Liberia?"},{"time":387964,"text":"Doctors Without Borders\nis an amazing organization,"},{"time":390664,"text":"dedicated and designed to provide\nemergency care in war zones."},{"time":395641,"text":"Liberia's civil war had ended in 2003 --"},{"time":398482,"text":"that was 11 years\nbefore Ebola even struck."},{"time":402632,"text":"When Ebola struck Liberia,"},{"time":404376,"text":"there were less than 50 doctors\nin the entire country"},{"time":408027,"text":"of 4.5 million people."},{"time":410709,"text":"Doctors Without Borders is in Liberia"},{"time":412917,"text":"because Liberia still doesn't really have\na functioning health system,"},{"time":416322,"text":"11 years later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418013,"text":"When the earthquake hit Haiti in 2010,"},{"time":421349,"text":"the outpouring of international\naid was phenomenal."},{"time":424906,"text":"But did you know that only\ntwo percent of that funding"},{"time":428601,"text":"went to rebuild\nHaitian public institutions,"},{"time":431467,"text":"including its health sector?"},{"time":433877,"text":"From that perspective,"},{"time":435318,"text":"Haitians continue to die\nfrom the earthquake even today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":439843,"text":"I recently met this gentleman."},{"time":441944,"text":"This is Dr. Nezar Ismet."},{"time":444046,"text":"He's the Minister of Health\nin the northern autonomous region of Iraq,"},{"time":447906,"text":"in Kurdistan."},{"time":449361,"text":"Here he is announcing\nthat in the last nine months,"},{"time":453267,"text":"his country, his region, has increased\nfrom four million people"},{"time":457333,"text":"to five million people."},{"time":458889,"text":"That's a 25 percent increase."},{"time":460781,"text":"Thousands of these new arrivals\nhave experienced incredible trauma."},{"time":465159,"text":"His doctors are working\n16-hour days without pay."},{"time":471047,"text":"His budget has not increased\nby 25 percent;"},{"time":473894,"text":"it has decreased by 20 percent,"},{"time":476313,"text":"as funding has flowed to security concerns\nand to short-term relief efforts."},{"time":481749,"text":"When his health sector fails --"},{"time":483377,"text":"and if history is any guide, it will --"},{"time":485814,"text":"how do you think that's going to influence"},{"time":487884,"text":"the decision making\nof the five million people in his region"},{"time":491140,"text":"as they think about\nwhether they should flee"},{"time":493983,"text":"that type of vulnerable living situation?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":497730,"text":"So as you can see,\nthis is a frustrating topic for me,"},{"time":500688,"text":"and I really try to understand:"},{"time":502214,"text":"Why the reluctance to protect and support"},{"time":505762,"text":"indigenous health systems\nand security systems?"},{"time":509422,"text":"I usually tier two concerns,\ntwo arguments."},{"time":512927,"text":"The first concern is about corruption,"},{"time":515138,"text":"and the concern that people\nin these settings are corrupt"},{"time":517881,"text":"and they are untrustworthy."},{"time":520256,"text":"And I will admit that I have met\nunsavory characters"},{"time":523341,"text":"working in health sectors\nin these situations."},{"time":525721,"text":"But I will tell you that the opposite\nis absolutely true"},{"time":529445,"text":"in every case I have worked on,"},{"time":531499,"text":"from Afghanistan to Libya, to Kosovo,\nto Haiti, to Liberia --"},{"time":535336,"text":"I have met inspiring people,"},{"time":537459,"text":"who, when the chips were down\nfor their country,"},{"time":539978,"text":"they risked everything\nto save their health institutions."},{"time":543311,"text":"The trick for the outsider\nwho wants to help"},{"time":546683,"text":"is identifying who those individuals are,"},{"time":549611,"text":"and building a pathway for them to lead."}]},{"cues":[{"time":551943,"text":"That is exactly what happened\nin Afghanistan."},{"time":555714,"text":"One of the unsung and untold\nsuccess stories"},{"time":559067,"text":"of our nation-building effort\nin Afghanistan"},{"time":562009,"text":"involved the World Bank in 2002\ninvesting heavily"},{"time":565529,"text":"in identifying, training and promoting\nAfghani health sector leaders."},{"time":572049,"text":"These health sector leaders\nhave pulled off an incredible feat"},{"time":575926,"text":"in Afghanistan."},{"time":577322,"text":"They have aggressively increased\naccess to health care"},{"time":581293,"text":"for the majority of the population."},{"time":583333,"text":"They are rapidly improving\nthe health status"},{"time":585561,"text":"of the Afghan population,"},{"time":586856,"text":"which used to be the worst in the world."},{"time":589945,"text":"In fact, the Afghan Ministry\nof Health does things"},{"time":592791,"text":"that I wish we would do in America."},{"time":594511,"text":"They use things like data to make policy."},{"time":596907,"text":"It's incredible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598116,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":600532,"text":"The other concern I hear a lot about is:"},{"time":602485,"text":"\"We just can't afford it,\nwe just don't have the money."},{"time":605111,"text":"It's just unsustainable.\""},{"time":607419,"text":"I would submit to you\nthat the current situation"},{"time":610176,"text":"and the current system we have"},{"time":611935,"text":"is the most expensive, inefficient system\nwe could possibly conceive of."},{"time":615997,"text":"The current situation\nis that when governments like the US --"},{"time":619399,"text":"or, let's say, the collection\nof governments"},{"time":621487,"text":"that make up the European Commission --"},{"time":623385,"text":"every year, they spend 15 billion dollars"},{"time":626058,"text":"on just humanitarian and emergency\nand disaster relief worldwide."},{"time":630088,"text":"That's nothing about foreign aid,\nthat's just disaster relief."},{"time":634075,"text":"Ninety-five percent of it\ngoes to international relief agencies,"},{"time":639144,"text":"that then have to import resources\ninto these areas,"},{"time":643505,"text":"and knit together some type\nof temporary health system, let's say,"},{"time":647918,"text":"which they then dismantle and send away\nwhen they run out of money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652181,"text":"So our job, it turns out, is very clear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657181,"text":"We, as the global health\ncommunity policy experts,"},{"time":661980,"text":"our first job is to become experts\nin how to monitor"},{"time":667549,"text":"the strengths and vulnerabilities\nof health systems"},{"time":670020,"text":"in threatened situations."},{"time":672611,"text":"And that's when we see doctors fleeing,"},{"time":674645,"text":"when we see health resources drying up,"},{"time":676606,"text":"when we see institutions crumbling --"},{"time":679065,"text":"that's the emergency."},{"time":680702,"text":"That's when we need to sound the alarm\nand wave our arms."},{"time":683836,"text":"OK?"},{"time":685254,"text":"Not now."},{"time":686429,"text":"Everyone can see that's an emergency,\nthey don't need us to tell them that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":691122,"text":"Number two:"},{"time":693085,"text":"places like where I work at Harvard\nneed to take their cue"},{"time":696446,"text":"from the World Bank experience\nin Afghanistan,"},{"time":698668,"text":"and we need to -- and we will --"},{"time":700349,"text":"build robust platforms to support\nhealth sector leaders like these."},{"time":706471,"text":"These people risk their lives."},{"time":708197,"text":"I think we can match their courage\nwith some support."}]},{"cues":[{"time":712425,"text":"Number three:"},{"time":713603,"text":"we need to reach out\nand make new partnerships."},{"time":716205,"text":"At our global health center,"},{"time":718103,"text":"we have launched a new initiative\nwith NATO and other security policy makers"},{"time":722139,"text":"to explore with them what they can do\nto protect health system institutions"},{"time":727529,"text":"during deployments."},{"time":729268,"text":"We want them to see"},{"time":730832,"text":"that protecting health systems\nand other critical social institutions"},{"time":735556,"text":"is an integral part of their mission."},{"time":738023,"text":"It's not just about avoiding\ncollateral damage;"},{"time":741184,"text":"it's about winning the peace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":744725,"text":"But the most important partner\nwe need to engage is you,"},{"time":748332,"text":"the American public,\nand indeed, the world public."},{"time":751788,"text":"Because unless you understand\nthe value of social institutions,"},{"time":757508,"text":"like health systems\nin these fragile settings,"},{"time":761066,"text":"you won't support efforts to save them."},{"time":763338,"text":"You won't click on that article"},{"time":765760,"text":"that talks about \"Hey, all those\ndoctors are on the run in country X."},{"time":770750,"text":"I wonder what that means."},{"time":773191,"text":"I wonder what that means"},{"time":775067,"text":"for that health system's ability\nto, let's say, detect influenza.\""},{"time":779853,"text":"\"Hmm, it's probably not good.\"\nThat's what I'd tell you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783770,"text":"Up on the screen,"},{"time":784958,"text":"I've put up my three favorite American\ninstitution defenders and builders."},{"time":791846,"text":"Over here is George C. Marshall,"},{"time":794755,"text":"he was the guy that proposed\nthe Marshall Plan"},{"time":797608,"text":"to save all of Europe's economic\ninstitutions after World War II."},{"time":802299,"text":"And this Eleanor Roosevelt."},{"time":804676,"text":"Her work on human rights\nreally serves as the foundation"},{"time":807846,"text":"for all of our international\nhuman rights organizations."},{"time":811330,"text":"Then my big favorite is Ben Franklin,"},{"time":813394,"text":"who did many things\nin terms of creating institutions,"},{"time":816626,"text":"but was the midwife of our constitution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":820582,"text":"And I would say to you"},{"time":822330,"text":"that these are folks who, when our\ncountry was threatened,"},{"time":826107,"text":"or our world was threatened,"},{"time":828138,"text":"they didn't retreat."},{"time":829465,"text":"They didn't talk about building walls."},{"time":831830,"text":"They talked about building institutions\nto protect human security,"},{"time":838008,"text":"for their generation and also for ours."},{"time":841194,"text":"And I think our generation\nshould do the same."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844683,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":845867,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}